'''Iwai''' (磐井, dates unknown - 22nd year of Emperor Keitai [528? <ref group="note" name="NihonShokiChronology"/>]), also known as '''Tsukushi Iwai''' (筑紫 磐井), was a regional chieftain in the early 6th century during the late [[Kofun period]]. His kabane was [[Kimi]]. 

In the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, his name is written as "Iwai"; in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, as "Tsukushi no Kimi Iwai"; and in the fragments of the {{ill|Chikugo no Kuni Fudoki|ja|筑後国風土記|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, as "Tsukushi Kimi Iwai." While the Nihon Shoki describes him as a Kuni no Miyatsuko of the [[Tsukushi Province]], some scholars suggest this was a later embellishment.<ref>{{Harv|Iwai Rebellion (Ancient History)|2006}}</ref><ref>{{Harv|Iwai (Ancient Clans)|2010}}</ref>

Iwai is known for leading the [[Iwai Rebellion]], as well as being one of the rare figures from this era whose tomb has been conclusively identified.

